@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Wedding Bouquet Ideas";
    Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_Layout.cshtml";
}

<section class="post-header">
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Wedding Bouquet Ideas</h1>
        <div class="post-meta">
            <span>May 10, 2024</span> •
            <span>4 min read</span>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="post-content">
    <div class="container">
        <img src="~/Images/blog/wedding-bouquets.jpg" alt="Wedding Bouquets" class="post-image">

        <div class="post-body">
            <p>Your wedding bouquet is more than flowers — it's a symbol of your theme, personality, and story. Here are beautiful bouquet ideas to inspire your special day.</p>

            <h2>Classic Round Bouquets</h2>
            <p>Perfect for traditional weddings, round bouquets often feature roses, peonies, or hydrangeas for a timeless look.</p>

            <h2>Garden-Inspired Bouquets</h2>
            <p>Loose, natural bouquets give a romantic, airy feel. These often include greenery, wildflowers, and soft pastel blooms.</p>

            <h2>Colorful & Modern Designs</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Vibrant seasonal flowers</li>
                <li>Unique shapes and asymmetrical arrangements</li>
                <li>Mix of bold tones with delicate blooms</li>
            </ul>

            <p>No matter your theme, the perfect bouquet will complement your dress, style, and the atmosphere of your wedding day.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="post-navigation">
            <a href="@Url.Action("Index", "Blog")" class="back-to-blog">← Back to Blog</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
